getCurrencyCodes has to return Observable so that you can subscribe to it. So you need to return Observable (in your mock or spyOn). Few examples:

```
class MockTradeService {
	getCurrencyCodes(): Observable&lt;number&gt; {
		return from([1, 4, 5]);
	}
}


```
You can use different Creators such as of, from, interval, range...
If you want mock function to be executed, then in your spyOn you have to add callThrough
```
spyOn(MockTradeService, &#39;getCurrencyCodes&#39;).and.callThrough();

```
If you want to return another value, then specify:
```
spyOn(MockTradeService, &#39;getCurrencyCodes&#39;).and.returnValue(from([9, 11, 7]));
```

